HEADWORD: Sarcosin
<hw>Sar"co*sin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline nitrogenous substance, formed in the
decomposition of creatin (one of the constituents of muscle tissue).
Chemically, it is methyl glycocoll.</def><-- N-Methylglycine, C3H7NO2.
-->⟦br⟧
